<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="546" pageId="7" pageNumber="544" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1919,2016]" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1919,1944]" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[360,421,1919,1944]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[436,535,1919,1944]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[371,1223,202,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[361,1234,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 5. Head of Mimaporia hmong. 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556281/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">Fig. 3–5</figureCitation>
). Antenna unipectinate, rami shorter in female. Compound eye black, about 1/2 length of head in lateral view. Ocelli absent. Chaetosemata absent. Labial palpus porrect, two-segmented. Proboscis well-developed and not covered with scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,320]" box="[199,1075,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis box="[199,280,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">Thorax</emphasis>
. Legs smoothly scaled. Epiphysis well developed. Spur formula 0-2-2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis box="[199,266,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[286,397,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,776,799]" captionTargetBox="[315,1251,221,684]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[313,1273,193,755]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 11. Wing pattern variations of Mimaporia hmong and the assumably closely related taxa. 6. M. hmong, holotype, male, Mt. Sapa (Vietnam: Lào Cai), coll. NSYSU; 7. M. hmong, paratype, female, Sapa (Vietnam: Lào Cai), coll. NSYSU; 8. M. hmong, paratype, male, Sapa (Vietnam: Lào Cai), coll. NSYSU; 9. M. sp., male, northern India, coll. NHM; 10. M. sp., female, northern India, coll. NHM. 11. M. sp., male, Wolong, (China: Sichuan), coll. NHM. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556282/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">Fig. 6–11</figureCitation>
). Forewing shape nearly triangular; termen slightly convex; retinaculum present in male; wing pattern with ground colour black, and with white stripes or dots at each cell. Hindwing nearly triangular; frenulum present in male, but absent in female; hair scales present on cells 1a+2a and 3a; coloration and maculation similar to that of forewing.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/556284/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="545" targetBox="[477,1111,388,1337]" targetPageId="8">
